Our client, a well-known Japanese company is currently looking for a Costing Officer.
Responsibilities

  Prepare monthly inventory report for WIP and FG items and verify the cost reasonableness of purchased and manufactured items in the division.
  Compute and maintain standard cost for all items manufactured in the division.
  Review and update standard cost for all items in system on a half-yearly basis.
  Perform standard cost simulation biannually and present change impact results to Accounts and the division in charge.
  Prepare quarterly forecast expenditure for factory overhead and manpower related expenses
  Consolidate all forecast plan from various departments to make division quarterly forecast plan for Accounts submission to headquarter.
  Perform monthly analysis on financial results and forecast of the division expenditure.
  Liaise with and provide support to external auditors in the course of their fieldwork.
  Coordinate half yearly stock take with various department.
  Reconcile differences in inventory report and division operating expenses.

Requirements

  Min Degree in Accountancy or equivalent.
  Min 3 years of working experience in related field is required for this position.
  Experience in auditing is preferred.

For interested parties, kindly send in your resume in MS Word format to eejing.loh@persolsg.com
We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.
